<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-321-146  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 321 146.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  April 9 1990 n295 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>U.S., Japan reach accord. (telecommunications trade issuessettled)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Poe, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US and Japan reach agreement on a number of telecommunicationstrade issues, including Japanese procurement of satellitetechnology from the US.andP;  Satellites are one of three key sectorsnamed as vital under the Super 301 provision of the Omnibus Tradeand Competitiveness Act of 1988.andP;  The terms of the agreement willmean that foreign companies will be permitted to bid on governmentor quasi-governmental satellite procurements for commercialpurposes.andP;  The agreement also calls for Japan to allow directsales of network channel terminating equipment from foreignsuppliers to Japanese end users.andP;  The Japanese negotiators alsoagreed to consider a US proposal to ease restrictions oninternational value-added network services such as internationalfacsimile transmissions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Statute:   Omnibus Trade and Competitiveness Act of 1988 (internationalaspects).andO;Topic:     United StatesJapanInternational CommunicationsInternational TradeSatellite CommunicationsValue-Added NetworksMarket Penetration.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>